  Finding Aids    Rare Books    Maps & GIS    Digital Images    Using Special Collections & University Archives    Special Collections Research Guides       Eyebrow menu    Contact Us    My Accounts    Give to the Library    COVID-19    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map    UIC Today     Toggle Search                  Breadcrumbs    Home    Help     Request items   Staff, students, faculty and emeritus faculty can request items from other libraries. I-Share will quickly deliver physical items from Illinois academic libraries. Interlibrary Loan (ILLiad) will allow you to request scanned articles and items not available in I-Share.       Log in to I-Share  Log in to ILLiad  If you have trouble logging in, you can set up a Library account .   How to request books and media in I-Share   Search I-Share for an item  Click on what you need!  Click “Request from I-Share Libraries” button  Log in, or create account   Register once by linking your UIC “Library ID Number” with your record.  You only need your NetID and password to order items.  Do you need your item sent to a library closer to you?  Change the “preferred pick-up location” to any institution participating in I-Share. You’ll get an email when the item is ready to pick up, usually in 3-5 business days.  How to request scanned articles and items from libraries worldwide in ILLiad   Login to ILLiad  Once you are logged into ILLiad click Find it @ UIC in library databases or in Google Scholar to pre-fill the request form for articles.  John Marshall Law School patrons can make ILL requests through a separate ILL system .  More help with ILLiad   Following the “Find it @ UIC” link is the simplest way to place a request. In Google Scholar, the link is sometimes hidden under the >> symbol.  You’ll get an email when the item is ready to pick up or posted electronically (usually 1-10 business days).  Most requests for physical items (books, DVDs, microfilm, etc.) are filled within 5-10 business days.  Most article requests are filled within 1-4 business days.  Articles are delivered as scanned PDFs.   Need help? Contact us or learn more about library accounts .      How Do I...?     Recommend an item for the library to purchase    Distance education user services    Search for articles, databases and journals    Search for books and e-books    Get textbooks    Make an appointment with a librarian    Order documents (alumni and non-UIC affiliates)     Get More Help        Filter by Location    Chicago-Daley    Chicago-Health Sciences    Peoria-Health Sciences    Rockford-Health Sciences    Urbana-Health Sciences      Filter by Topic    Accessibility    Borrowing    Computers, Printing & Scanning    Copyright & Scholarly Publishing    Course Reserves    Electronic Resources    Library Accounts    Off-Campus Access    Requesting Materials    Research Help    Searching    Special Collections & University Archives    Study Spaces    Uncategorized    Writing, Style & Citations            Need help?  Contact a Librarian!                 Logo for the University of Illinois at Chicago       University  Library          Locations           Richard J. Daley Library    801 S. Morgan   Chicago , IL  60607       Circulation  (312) 996-2724    Reference  (312) 996-2726    Special Collections & University Archives  (312) 996-2742    Course Reserves  (312) 996-2719                             Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago    1750 W. Polk St.   Chicago , IL  60612       Circulation  (312) 996-8966    Reference  (312) 996-9163    Special Collections & University Archives  (312) 996-8977    Course Reserves  (312) 996-8963                             Library of the Health Sciences-Peoria    One Illini Drive   Peoria , IL  61605       Phone  (309) 671-8490                        Crawford Library of the Health Sciences-Rockford    1601 Parkview Ave.   Rockford , IL  61107       Phone  (815) 395-5650                             Library of the Health Sciences-Urbana    470 Grainger Engineering Libr